This project involves a traffic and pedestrian light system that includes a timer for the pedestrian signal.

The timer counts down from 9 to 0, after which the pedestrian light turns green, allowing pedestrians to

cross. When the push button is pressed and held, the pedestrian light switches to green as quickly as

possible. The green pedestrian signal then flashes on and off to indicate that the button has been

activated.


